The Constitutional Court in the land is scheduled to hand down judgment on the constitutionality of the Electoral Act. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - The Constitutional Court is scheduled to hand down judgment on the constitutionality of the Electoral Act. The little known NGO New Nation Movement wants the electoral Act to be amended to allow independent candidates to run in provincial and national elections. Currently, the Electoral Act only allows political parties to contest. READ: Judgment reserved in tobacco case Independent candidates are only permitted to contest for local government. The highest court in the land says attendance at this hand down will be limited to 20 members of the public, including the media.